The paper presents a method for accurate mapping using aerial robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method employs visual-inertial odometry and point cloud processing, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the expected geometric stability of the ICP step, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, and can be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
